SIMPLE: putter
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Putter
<hw>Put"ter</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who
puts or plates.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Specifically, one who pushes the small wagons in a
coal mine, and the like.</def> <mark>[Prov. Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Putter</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Putter
<hw>Putt"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Golf)</fld>
<sd>(a)</sd> <def>A club with a short shaft and either a wooden or a
metal head, used in putting.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>One who
putts.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Putter</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Putter
<hw>Put"ter</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Puttered</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Puttering</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[See
<er>Potter</er>.]</ety> <def>To act inefficiently or idly; to occupy
oneself in a leisurely manner; to trifle; to potter; <as>as, to
<ex>putter</ex> around in the garden</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Putter-on</ent>⟦br⟧
